'''Scott Brumfield''' (born August 19, 1970) is a former professional football player. Brumfield was an [[Offensive Guard]] for the [[Cincinnati Bengals]]. He was not [[NFL Draft|drafted]], but later signed on to the Bengals as a [[Free agent (football)|free-agent]] in 1996. He played six seasons in the [[NFL]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Through Hundreds of Hours of Rehabilitation, Former BYU Lineman Scott Brumfield Is . . . MAKING STRIDES; Brumfield Regaining Life After Injury|date=April 7, 1997|work=Salt Lake Tribune|accessdate=2 December 2010}}</ref> Brumfield suffered a severe spinal-cord injury that left his legs temporarily paralyzed in the third quarter of a game in [[Baltimore]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Back on his Feet; Bengals' Brumfield beats paralysis|last=Coffey|first=Wayne|date=August 10, 1997|work=Florida Times-Union|accessdate=2 December 2010}}</ref> After requiring the use of crutches to walk for several months, he rehabilitated and returned to play for the Bengals.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bengals Re-Sign Brumfield|last=Marvez|first=Alex|date=April 18, 1997|work=Dayton Daily News|accessdate=2 December 2010}}</ref>

